HEADWORD: obsessed
<hw>obsessed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having or showing
excessive or compulsive concern; -- used with
<ptcl>with</ptcl>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> haunted, preoccupied, taken up(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>influenced or controlled by a powerful force such as
a strong emotion.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> possessed(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obsession</ent>⟦br⟧
